<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880310-0016 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Strober Organization Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> STRB </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Strober Organization Inc., a Brooklyn, N.Y.-based supplier of building materials, said the company may be sold.    According to a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Sue Strober, who is the beneficiary of the estate of Eric D. Strober and holds 2,999,710 shares, or 49% of the company, said that she and the management and the board of the company may consider a sale of the concern.    In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Stober closed at $12, up $2.    Attempts to get further comment from Ms. Strober were unsuccessful.    An official of the company said the concern had no immediate comment on the filing. </TEXT></DOC>